		script(src="webcomponentsjs/webcomponents-lite.min.js")
		<link rel="import" href="/polymer/polymer.html">

		<link rel="import" href="/paper-toolbar/paper-toolbar.html">
		<link rel="import" href="/paper-card/paper-card.html">
		<link rel="import" href="/paper-button/paper-button.html">

		style(is="custom-style").
			body {
				background-color: #6B4E4E;
				font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
				font-size: 125%;
			}

			paper-card {
				margin-top: 10px;
				width:380px;
				background-color: #e57373;
			}

			a {
				color: black;
				text-decoration:none;
			}

			paper-button.highlight {
				margin-top: auto;
				background-color: #1976d2;
				color: white;
			}

			paper-button.dark-highlight {
				background-color: #6B4E4E;
				color: white;
			}

			.container {
				margin: 0 auto;
				margin-top: 20px;
				width: 80%;
				display: flex;
				flex-direction: row;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-content: center;
				align-items: flex-start;
			}

			.card-content {
				text-align:center;
				background-color: #e57373;
				color: white;
			}

			.content-container {
				height:100%;	
				display: flex;
				flex-direction: column;
				justify-content: space-between;
			}

			p {
				text-align: justify;
			}

			.liquidjs {
				width: 100%;
			}

			.liquidjs .card-content .logo {
				width: 100%;
			}

			.liquidjs .card-content .devices {
				width: 50%;
			}

			#toolbar {
				width:80%;
				margin:auto;
				background-color: #e57373;
			}

			.center {
				margin:auto;
			}

			li {
				text-align: justify;
				margin-top: 0.5em;
			}

			.toolbar-link {
				margin-top: 5px;
				margin-bottom: 5px;
				width: 200px;
			}

		title.
			Welcome

	body
		div#toolbar.container
			div.center
				a(href="/")
					paper-button.dark-highlight.toolbar-link.
						Card game
				a(href="/photo")
					paper-button.dark-highlight.toolbar-link.
						Photo Filtering
				a(href="/chat")
					paper-button.dark-highlight.toolbar-link.
						Chat Migration
				a(href="/editor")
					paper-button.dark-highlight.toolbar-link.
						Editor

		div.container
			paper-card(image="images/chat.png")
				div.card-content
					div.content-container
						h2.
							Chat
						p.
							Enter as a device owning the chat component.
						a(href="/chat/client")
							paper-button.highlight.
								Connect

			paper-card(image="images/device.png")
				div.card-content
					div.content-container
						h2.
							Add Device
						p.
							Enter as a device without owning the chat component.
						a(href="/chat/device")
							paper-button.highlight.
								Connect

		div.container
			paper-card.liquidjs
				div.card-content
					h3.
						The Framework

					img.logo(src="images/liquidLogo2.png")

					p.
						Liquid.js is a Web framework for creating component-based applications able to seamlessly flow between multiple heterogeneous devices following the user attention. Users owning multiple devices can take advantage of running liquid Web applications taking full advantage of all of their devices. 
						
					p.
						Liquid applications are meant to run sequentially or in parallel on a dynamic set of devices connected in a Peer to Peer mesh. Developers aiming to add liquid behaviors on top of their Polymer applications can take advantage of the APIs provided by the framework in order to migrate, fork or clone their already built Web components. Stateful components are automatically and transparently syncrhonised between devices without relying on a centralized master copy deployed in the Cloud.

					p.
						Liquid.js is built on Polymer, WebRTC and Yjs.

					img.devices(src="images/liquidDevices.png")

					h1.
						Publications

					ul
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, <strong>Migrating and Pairing Recursive Stateful Components Between Multiple Devices with Liquid.js for Polymer</strong>, 16th International Conference on Web Engineering (ICWE 2016), Switzerland, Italy, Springer, May, 2016 
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, and Cesare Pautasso, <strong>Deploying Stateful Web Components on Multiple Devices with Liquid.js for Polymer</strong>, 19th International ACM Sigsoft Symposium on Component-Based Software Engineering (CBSE 2016), Venice, Italy, pp. 85-90, April, 2016
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, and Cesare Pautasso, <strong>The Liquid.js Framework for Migrating and Cloning Stateful Web Components across Multiple Devices</strong>, Proc. of the 25th International World Wide Web conference (WWW 2016), Montreal, Canada, ACM, pp. 183-186, April, 2016

					h1.
						Liquid software publications by us


					ul
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, Cesare Pautasso, Ville Ilvonen, Tommi Mikkonen, Kari Systa, Jari-Pekka Voutilainen, and Antero Taivalsaari, <strong>Architecting Liquid Software</strong>, Journal of Web Engineering, In press, 2017.
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, and Cesare Pautasso, <strong>Maturity Model for Liquid Web Architectures</strong>, 17th International Conference on Web Engineering (ICWE 2017), Rome, Italy, Springer, June, 2017.
						li.
							Andrea Gallidabino, Cesare Pautasso, Ville Ilvonen, Tommi Mikkonen, Kari Systa, Jari-Pekka Voutilainen, and Antero Taivalsaari, <strong>On the Architecture of Liquid Software: Technology Alternatives and Design Space</strong>, 13th Working IEEE/IFIP Conference on Software Architecture (WICSA 2016), Venice, Italy, April, 2016

